9    /**
10    * This assigner is able to handle the {@code void} type. This means:
11    * <ol>
12    * <li>If a {@code void} type is assigned to the {@code void} it will consider this a trivial operation.</li>
13    * <li>If a {@code void} type is assigned to a non-{@code void} type, it will pop the top value from the stack.</li>
14    * <li>If a non-{@code void} type is assigned to a {@code void} type, it will load the target type's default value
15    * only if this was configured at the assigner's construction.</li>
16    * <li>If two non-{@code void} types are subject of the assignment, it will delegate the assignment to its chained
17    * assigner.</li>
18    * </ol>
19    */
